# Sets the number of server alive messages (see below) which may be sent
# without ssh(1) receiving any messages back from the server.  If this
# threshold is reached while server alive messages are being sent, ssh will
# disconnect from the server, terminating the session.
#
# If, for example, ServerAliveInterval (see below) is set to 10 and
# ServerAliveCountMax is set to 2, if the server becomes unresponsive,
# ssh will disconnect after approximately 20 seconds.
ServerAliveCountMax 2
ServerAliveInterval 10
TCPKeepAlive yes

UseRoaming no
VisualHostKey yes
